    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the style and culture of the Wet'suwet'en, formerly known as the Broman Lake Indian Band, whose traditional territories are in present-day central British Columbia. The Wet'suwet'en First Nation is a member of the Carrier Sekani Tribal Council.</Note_Text>
